The paper discusses automated temporal planning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) that deals with planning and scheduling actions over time. The paper also mentions heuristic-search techniques, which are commonly used in planning algorithms and fall under the category of programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The paper's focus on controlling systems and modeling actions suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper's experimental evaluation and comparison with other approaches suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
